@api @notes
Feature: Notes Management

  As an authenticated user
  I want to create, view, update and delete my notes
  So that I can keep my personal information organized

  Background:
    Given an authenticated user exists


  @smoke @positive
  Scenario: User creates a new note successfully
    When the user creates a note with title "Shopping List" and description "Buy milk"
    Then the note should be created successfully
    And the note should be available in the user's notes list


  @positive
  Scenario: User retrieves note details
    Given the user has a note with title "Daily Plan" and description "Team meeting at 10"
    When the user retrieves the note details
    Then the note details should include title "Daily Plan"
    And the note details should include description "Team meeting at 10"


  @positive
  Scenario: User updates an existing note
    Given the user has a note with title "Old Title" and description "Old Description"
    When the user updates the note title to "Updated Title" and description to "Updated Description"
    Then the note should be updated successfully
    And the note should be available with title "Updated Title"
    And the note should be available with description "Updated Description"


  @positive
  Scenario: User deletes an existing note
    Given the user has a note with title "Temporary Note" and description "This note will be deleted"
    When the user deletes the note
    Then the note should be deleted successfully
    But the note should not be available in the user's notes list


  @negative @validation
  Scenario Outline: Note creation is rejected when required information is missing
    When the user tries to create a note with title "<title>" and description "<description>"
    Then the note creation should be rejected
    And the error message should mention "<missing_field>"

    Examples:
      | title         | description | missing_field |
      |               | Buy milk    | title         |
      | Shopping List |             | description   |


  @negative @auth
  Scenario: Unauthenticated user cannot create a note
    Given the user is not authenticated
    When the user tries to create a note with title "Private Note" and description "Secret"
    Then the note creation should be rejected
    And the user should be asked to authenticate


  @negative @auth
  Scenario: Unauthenticated user cannot retrieve notes
    Given the user is not authenticated
    When the user tries to retrieve notes
    Then the request should be rejected
    And the user should be asked to authenticate



Bu senaryolarda POST /notes, GET /notes/{id} gibi endpoint detaylarını feature dosyasına yazmadık. 
